summary: Oh man, I just had the best idea for a fan fiction... Avengers Dirty Rotten Scoundrels AU. (While I’ve seen the DRS movie, the...
body:
Oh man, I just had the best idea for a fan fiction… Avengers Dirty Rotten Scoundrels AU. (While I’ve seen the DRS movie, the musical is waaaaay better, and the West End version trumps the Broadway version every time)

But just pictures it: 

Tony Stark, the well dressed, well established, high class con man, who has everyone eating out of his palm but who’s bored with running the same con over and over, however successful it may be.

Enter Clint Carton, the scruffy, crane born con man who Tony laughs at and looks down his nose at, before trying to trick Clint into leaving his territory. Only Clint isn’t as dumb as he looks, so he challenges Tony to a contest. 

The target: Steve Rogers. a blushing, innocent heir of a soap fortune, so clean cut you get could a paper cut from him. 

The aim: fifty thousand dollars.

Tony and Clint throw their best at Steve, and Tony is pissed to realise that Clint is worming his way into Steve’s affections - which is doubly annoying because Steve Rogers is kinda hot and adorable, and Tony kinda wants him for real. And because Tony Stark does have a heart, he sends Steve away, trying to protect him. Only Steve comes back and goes to Clint. And Clint’s pretty certain he’s in, although he’s kinda freaked at Steve saying “I love you” but hey, he gets the money and he gets laid? Sweet. 

Then Steve turns up at Tony’s and tells him that Clint slept with him then stole his fifty thousand dollars. Tony feels awful, so he gives Steve fifty thousand dollars and sends him on his way. Then Clint turns up, revealing that he got knocked out, and when he woke his clothes and Steve were gone. He denies stealing Steve’s money, which is when they find Clint’s suitcase, containing a note from Steve revealing himself as The Captain, the con man Tony had previously mistaken Clint for. Clint is furious, but Tony is delighted and pretty much in love by now. 

Clint and Tony decide they make a pretty good team and spend the rest of the summer working together. Until one afternoon, suddenly there are people in Tony’s house, being led by Steve Rogers who is, apparently, selling the house. Steve pulls Tony and Clint into the con, and the three of them set off to do great things together, but not before Tony and Steve make out while Clint looks bored.

I just love this because it would be a perfect story to show off how much of an asshole Steve really is behind that All American Exterior. I have way too many ideas at the moment, but if someone wanted to write this, that would be awesome.

summary:
Avengers: Infinity War, directed by Anthony Russo & Joe Russo.

This is Thanos's story, this is his movie. 😎

Infinity War is a...
caption:
Avengers: Infinity War, directed by Anthony Russo & Joe Russo.

This is Thanos’s story, this is his movie. 😎

Infinity War is a tremendously fun time at the cinemas. It is quite literally an ‘Epic’, sprawling across so many characters, universes, worlds, tones, etc. This film feels like an event, which it may very well be, and I can safely say the Russo Brothers and writers Markus and McFeely as well pulled off a miracle and made such a Herculean task of a film into something I think is a great summer blockbuster. 🤩💰 Now with some of the bad stuff which I think I only noticed while watching. The movie is made on 300-400 million USD and at some point, the film suffers bad cinematography, poor CGI and choppy cuts. There are sequences where it simply feels too long or too short in places. 😭

Let’s get back to good side. 😊 Every character gets their own moment to shine a little, It was such a joy to see all the Avengers on screen together again. Josh Brolin gives an amazing performance as Thanos, who is much more layered than I thought. 😍

Overall, Avengers: Infinity War is another great addition to the Marvel Cinematic Universe. 10 years in the making … it’s worth the wait!👍 My rating ⭐️ ⭐️ ⭐️ ⭐️ 4/5 😎
.
.

summary:
Y'ALL KNOW WHAT I FUCKING WANT IN AVENGERS 4???
The Avengers, the Guardians and Captain Marvel's final showdown with Thanos....
body:
Y'ALL KNOW WHAT I FUCKING WANT IN AVENGERS 4???

The Avengers, the Guardians and Captain Marvel’s final showdown with Thanos. Everyone is beating Thanos from left to right until the gauntlet is finally out of his hand. They still continue to bring him down, one by one. Each one gets a piece of him. All of them fought aggressively, unforgiving, and vengeful against the Titan. One final blow knocked him off his feet. Thanos lays broken, exhausted and beaten on the ground. It was all black for a brief moment until he comes back again. As he flicker his eyes open, he first saw the bright sun blinding his eyes. He closed them again, then open. The last thing he saw was his adversaries, standing in front of him, weapons at the ready,

ready to take him down for good.

body:
So I was talking to my 11 yr old brother about Thanos and the infinity gauntlet today and suddenly…

Him: he could be watching a tv show and be like “No! Maria why won’t you marry him?!” And then be like “oh wait.” *clicks fingers* “Yes Maria marry him.”
